EPresident%20Jimmy%20Carter%2C%20who%20had%20served%20in%20the%20US%20Navy%2C%20was%20instrumental%20in%20countering%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20rising%20extremism%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3Cp%3EPhotoQuest%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPerceptions%20of%20weakness%20dogged%20Jimmy%20Carter's%20presidency%20and%20legacy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECarter%20inherited%20a%20struggling%20economy%20and%20a%20US%20military%20adrift%20after%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20his%20administration%20played%20key%20parts%20in%20countering%20the%20Soviets%20and%20rising%20extremism.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20dissolved%20in%201991%2C%20the%20man%20who%20received%20the%20most%20credit%20was%20Ronald%20Reagan.%20The%20Republican%20president's%20bellicose%20policies%20and%20tough%20rhetoric%20%E2%80%94%20he%20called%20it%20an%20%26quot%3Bevil%20empire%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20were%20seen%20as%20ultimately%20forcing%20the%20Soviets%20into%20an%20arms%20race%20they%20couldn't%20afford.%20And%20Reagan%20seemed%20particularly%20strong%20compared%20to%20his%20predecessor%2C%20Jimmy%20Carter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlmost%20from%20the%20start%20of%20his%20Democratic%20administration%20in%201977%2C%20Carter%20was%20criticized%20for%20being%20weak%20on%20national%20security.%20Never%20mind%20that%20he%20was%20an%20Annapolis%20graduate%20who%20served%20as%20a%20US%20Navy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2024%2F12%2F29%2Fjimmy-carter-39th-u-s-president-and-submariner-dies-at-100%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esubmarine%20officer%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20including%20being%20selected%20for%20duty%20on%20new%20nuclear-powered%20submarines.%20But%20these%20perceptions%20of%20his%20supposed%20weakness%20bear%20revisiting%20after%20his%20December%2029%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjimmy-carter-dead-president-humanitarian-obituary-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeath%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20as%20Carter%20played%20key%20roles%20in%20countering%20the%20Soviets%20and%20Islamist%20extremists%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECarter%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20his%20predecessor%20Gerald%20Ford%20%E2%80%94%20had%20the%20misfortune%20of%20inheriting%20a%20national%20security%20mess.%20The%20US%20military%20of%20the%20late%201970s%20was%20called%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsgp.fas.org%2Fcrs%2Fnatsec%2FR42334.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Bhollow%20force%3A%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Strong%20on%20paper%20but%20crippled%20by%20poor%20readiness%2C%20racial%20tensions%2C%20and%20unmotivated%20recruits%20who%20dabbled%20in%20drugs%20as%20the%20armed%20forces%20shifted%20to%20an%20all-volunteer%20force.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBattered%20by%20inflation%2C%20soaring%20gas%20prices%2C%20and%20the%20lingering%20trauma%20of%20Vietnam%2C%20the%20American%20public%20was%20not%20inclined%20toward%20more%20war%20or%20defense%20spending.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20appeared%20to%20be%20at%20the%20height%20of%20its%20power%2C%20as%20Moscow%20fielded%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.defense.gov%2FPortals%2F70%2FDocuments%2Fsecretaryofdefense%2FOSDSeries_Vol8_Chapter2.pdf%3Fver%3DaHVOORslLp8fLiuwnzNVmg%253D%253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%20missiles%20and%20tanks%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20Soviet%20and%20Cuban%20forces%20intervened%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fmilestones%2F1969-1976%2Fangola%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAngolan%20Civil%20War%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECarter%20entered%20the%20White%20House%20with%20a%20moralist%20vision%20of%20foreign%20policy%2C%20the%20polar%20opposite%20of%20Richard%20Nixon's%20and%20Henry%20Kissinger's%20realpolitik.%20He%20wanted%20to%20emphasize%20human%20rights%20and%20international%20cooperation.%20But%20like%20previous%20high-minded%20presidents%20such%20as%20Harry%20S.%20Truman%2C%20he%20evolved%20into%20more%20of%20a%20hawk.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20he%20had%20campaigned%20in%201976%20on%20a%20pledge%20to%20cut%20the%20defense%20budget%2C%20Carter%20oversaw%20a%20defense%20buildup%20that%20by%201980%20called%20for%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F1980%2F01%2F29%2Fcarter-is-converted-to-a-big-spender-on-defense-projects%2F6a04fed3-ca48-433e-a972-cca13bdf83a0%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E14%25%20annual%20budget%20increase%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(actually%20closer%20to%205%25%20after%20inflation).%20This%20included%20new%20M1%20tanks%2C%20cargo%20planes%2C%20a%20new%20ICBM%20(the%20MX%2C%20which%20was%20eventually%20canceled)%2C%20and%20higher%20pay%20for%20military%20personnel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20canceled%20what%20he%20saw%20as%20boondoggles%2C%20such%20as%20the%20B-1%20bomber.%20He%20also%20ended%20the%20controversial%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadst.org%2F2016%2F07%2Fthe-neutron-bomb-a-negotiating-dud%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eneutron%20bomb%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20project%2C%20a%20small%20nuclear%20weapon%20that%20produced%20more%20radiation%20than%20blast%2C%20and%20which%20detractors%20saw%20as%20the%20ultimate%20capitalist%20weapon%20(it%20%26quot%3Bseems%20desirable%20to%20those%20who%20worry%20about%20property%20and%20hold%20life%20cheap%2C%26quot%3B%20warned%20science-fiction%20author%20Isaac%20Asimov).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20pre-green%20energy%20days%20of%20the%201970s%2C%20securing%20the%20West's%20oil%20supply%20was%20paramount.%20Worried%20that%201979%20Soviet%20invasion%20of%20Afghanistan%20created%20a%20springboard%20for%20a%20Soviet%20invasion%20through%20Iran%20and%20Afghanistan%20to%20the%20oil-rich%20Persian%20Gulf%2C%20Carter%20laid%20down%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.state.gov%2Fhistoricaldocuments%2Ffrus1977-80v18%2Fd45%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BCarter%20Doctrine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BLet%20our%20position%20be%20absolutely%20clear%2C%26quot%3B%20Carter%20warned%20in%20his%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20address%20on%20Jan.%2023%2C%201980.%20%26quot%3BAn%20attempt%20by%20any%20outside%20force%20to%20gain%20control%20of%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%20region%20will%20be%20regarded%20as%20an%20assault%20on%20the%20vital%20interests%20of%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%2C%20and%20such%20an%20assault%20will%20be%20repelled%20by%20any%20means%20necessary%2C%20including%20military%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Carter's%20presidency%20and%20reelection%20campaign%20was%20dogged%20by%20the%20taking%20of%20American%20hostages%20at%20the%20US%20Embassy%20in%20Tehran.%20Most%20were%20held%20for%20444%20days.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677c52d54fdf00939ed67fd2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221430%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarter's%20presidency%20and%20reelection%20campaign%20was%20dogged%20by%20the%20taking%20of%20American%20hostages%20at%20the%20US%20Embassy%20in%20Tehran.%20Most%20were%20held%20for%20444%20days.%3Cp%3EUPI%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Carter%20administration%20created%20the%20Rapid%20Deployment%20Force%2C%20which%20could%20be%20dispatched%20to%20any%20crisis%20zone%20in%20the%20world%20(though%20it%20was%20really%20aimed%20at%20the%20Persian%20Gulf).%20On%20paper%2C%20it%20seemed%20a%20powerful%20force%3A%20the%2082nd%20Airborne%20and%20101st%20Airmobile%20Divisions%2C%20a%20Marine%20division%20and%20%26quot%3Blight%26quot%3B%20Army%20divisions%2C%20all%20backed%20by%20Navy%20carriers%20and%20Air%20Force%20fighter%20wings.%20Yet%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbo.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F98th-congress-1983-1984%2Freports%2Fdoc07a_2.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecritics%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20questioned%20how%20rapid%20the%20RDF%20could%20be%20given%20limited%20transport%20capacity%2C%20and%20wondered%20how%20lightly%20armed%20paratroopers%20and%20Marines%20would%20fare%20in%20the%20desert%20against%20Soviet%20armor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECarter%20sought%20strategic%20arms%20control%20through%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F2009-2017.state.gov%2Ft%2Fisn%2F5195.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESALT%20II%20treaty%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20(he%20asked%20the%20Senate%20not%20to%20ratify%20the%20treaty%20after%20the%20Soviet%20invasion%20of%20Afghanistan).%20Yet%20after%20Moscow%20deployed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Farticle%2Fthe-euromissile-showdown%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESS-20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20intermediate-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20in%20Eastern%20Europe%2C%20Carter%20responded%20by%20calling%20for%20both%20diplomacy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20US%20Pershing%20II%20missiles%20to%20be%20stationed%20in%20Western%20Europe.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECarter's%20critics%20lambasted%20his%20emphasis%20on%20human%20rights%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Helsinki%20Accords%2C%20as%20hopelessly%20naive.%20Yet%20a%20focus%20on%20human%20rights%20spurred%20dissidents%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atlanticcouncil.org%2Fblogs%2Fnew-atlanticist%2Fhow-jimmy-carters-support-for-human-rights-helped-win-the-cold-war%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESolidarity%20movement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Poland%2C%20that%20ultimately%20weakened%20the%20Soviet%20empire.%20The%20Camp%20David%20Accords%2C%20which%20brokered%20peace%20between%20Israel%20and%20Egypt%2C%20dampened%20Soviet%20influence%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20turned%20Moscow's%20former%20client%20Egypt%20into%20an%20American%20ally.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20Carter%20fell%20victim%20to%20the%20perception%20that%20he%20was%20a%20weak%20president.%20His%20biggest%20albatross%20was%20Iran's%20444-day%20seizure%20of%20the%20US%20Embassy%20in%20Tehran%3A%20even%20when%20Carter%20authorized%20a%20risky%20rescue%20mission%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-failed-iran-hostage-rescue-raid-influenced-us-special-forces-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebotched%20operation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20free%2052%20Americans%20failed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAgainst%20a%20vigorous%20and%20masterful%20communicator%20like%20Ronald%20Reagan%2C%20who%20touted%20military%20strength%20and%20confrontation%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20as%20more%20than%20a%20necessity%20but%20a%20virtue%2C%20Carter%20appeared%20lacking.%20He%20was%20defeated%20by%20a%20landslide%20in%20the%201980%20election.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20were%20many%20reasons%20why%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20collapsed.%20The%20biggest%20cause%20was%20the%20decrepit%20Soviet%20economy%3B%20Mikhail%20Gorbachev%20and%20the%20new%20generation%20of%20Soviet%20leaders%20recognized%20it%20was%20not%20sustainable%2C%20but%20failed%20to%20reform%20it%20in%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20say%20that%20Jimmy%20Carter%20%E2%80%94%20or%20Ronald%20Reagan%20%E2%80%94%20were%20instrumental%20by%20themselves%20in%20defeating%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20would%20be%20an%20exaggeration.%20It%20is%20more%20accurate%20to%20say%20that%20Carter%20continued%20a%20tradition%20%E2%80%94%20dating%20back%20to%20Truman%20and%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20%E2%80%94%20of%20confronting%20the%20Soviet%20threat.%20Carter%20doesn't%20deserve%20all%20the%20credit%2C%20but%20he%20deserves%20his%20share.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20an%20MA%20in%20political%20science%20from%20Rutgers%20Univ.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ETwitter%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmipeck%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjimmy-carter-deserves-some-credit-for-winning-the-cold-war-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736208901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F677c53794fdf00939ed6802c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjimmy-carter-deserves-some-credit-for-winning-the-cold-war-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20legacy%20of%20Jimmy%20Carter's%20administration%20includes%20key%20roles%20in%20countering%20the%20Soviets%20and%20Islamist%20extremists%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Michael%20Peck)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A44%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjimmy-car