st%20important%20thing%20to%20do%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fnorovirus-treatment%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eif%20you%20become%20sick%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENorovirus%2C%20commonly%20called%20the%20stomach%20flu%20or%20the%2024-hour%20bug%2C%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20across%20the%20US%20this%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20Norovirus%20outbreaks%20%E2%80%94%20which%20are%20most%20common%20from%20November%20to%20April%20%E2%80%94%20have%20reached%20one%20of%20their%20highest%20levels%20from%20any%20time%20in%20the%20past%2012%20years%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnorovirus%2Fphp%2Freporting%2Fnorostat-data-table.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECenters%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20most%20recent%20data%20available%2C%20the%20CDC%20reported%2091%20norovirus%20outbreaks%20across%20the%20US%20for%20the%20first%20week%20of%20December%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20outbreaks%20for%20the%20same%20week%20since%202012%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnorovirus%2Fphp%2Freporting%2Fnorostat-data.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efourth-highest%20number%20of%20outbreaks%3C%2Fa%3E%20recorded%20in%20any%20week%20of%20the%20year%20since%202012.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CDC%20defines%20an%20outbreak%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20occurrence%20of%20two%20or%20more%20similar%20illnesses%20resulting%20from%20a%20common%20exposure%20that%20is%20either%20suspected%20or%20laboratory-confirmed%20to%20be%20caused%20by%20norovirus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20norovirus%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22181dee44-a10c-4b9b-9bba-2695e0ba688a%5C%22%3ENorovirus%20symptoms%2C%20treatment%2C%20and%20prevention%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-norovirus-spreads-cdc-symptoms-lysol-hand-sanitizer-stomach-bug-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorovirus%3C%2Fa%3E%20presents%20itself%20much%20like%20food%20poisoning%20%E2%80%94%20with%20a%20rapid%20onset%20of%20nausea%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20vomiting%2C%20and%20stomach%20pain%20that%20generally%20lasts%20between%20one%20and%20three%20days.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20a%20few%20key%20differences%20between%20the%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20it%20spreads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Once%20someone%20becomes%20exposed%20to%20norovirus%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20spread%20through%20direct%20contact%20and%20can%20linger%20on%20surfaces%20for%20days%20or%20even%20weeks%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20become%20infected%20within%20a%20day%20or%20two.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20symptoms%20of%20food%20poisoning%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20will%20typically%20present%20much%20faster%20than%20that%2C%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20hours%2C%20said%20Dr.%20Shruti%20Gohil%2C%20a%20professor%20and%20the%20associate%20medical%20director%20of%20epidemiology%20and%20infection%20prevention%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine's%20School%20of%20Medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20treat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Though%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fnorovirus-treatment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etreatments%20for%20both%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20be%20similar%20%E2%80%94%20drinking%20water%2C%20eating%20bland%20foods%2C%20taking%20anti-diarrheal%20medication%20%E2%80%94%20Gohil%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20in%20doubt%2C%20you%20should%20act%20as%20if%20you%20have%20norovirus.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20of%20how%20highly%20contagious%20norovirus%20is%20compared%20to%20food%20poisoning.%20Norovirus%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20contagious%20infections%20we%20know%20of%2C%20and%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorovirus-outbreak-spread-contagious-infectious-disease-doctor-advice-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelp%20prevent%20its%20spread%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20vigilant%20about%20washing%20your%20hands%20and%20disinfecting%20surfaces%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20to%20do%20if%20you're%20experiencing%20symptoms%20is%20to%20stay%20hydrated.%20When%20you're%20losing%20so%20much%20fluid%2C%20particularly%20if%20you%20can't%20keep%20any%20fluids%20down%2C%20there's%20a%20risk%20of%20dehydration%2C%20which%20can%20become%20life-threatening%2C%20Gohil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELook%20for%20these%20symptoms%20as%20warning%20flags%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20If%20you%20reach%20the%20point%20of%20dizziness%20or%20light-headedness%2C%20Gohil%20said%2C%20then%20you%20may%20be%20dangerously%20dehydrated%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20you%20need%20to%20get%20yourself%20to%20an%20ER.%20When%20you%20get%20a%20headache%2C%20that's%20an%20early%20warning%20sign%20of%20dehydration%20and%20an%20indicator%20that%20you%20need%20to%20increase%20your%20fluid%20intake%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20are%20very%20young%2C%20very%20old%2C%20or%20immunocompromised%20can%20have%20infections%20that%20last%20longer%2C%20and%20they%20may%20be%20at%20higher%20risk%20of%20dehydration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPay%20special%20attention%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Gohil%20also%20mentioned%20a%20few%20signs%20of%20dehydration%20to%20look%20out%20for%20in%20people%20who%20can't%20speak%20for%20themselves%2C%20like%20babies%20and%20nonverbal%20seniors.%20And%20that's%20if%20they%20cannot%20form%20tears%2C%20if%20their%20mouth%20looks%20dry%2C%20if%20they're%20despondent%2C%20or%20if%20they're%20not%20really%20reacting%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b488a33-8cb4-4480-8114-6a6c04e38f64%5C%22%3EWhy%20norovirus%20is%20so%20bad%20this%20year%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20norovirus%20outbreaks%2C%20Gohil%20said%20it's%20pretty%20bad%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20main%20reasons%20for%20that%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20that%20more%20and%20more%20people%20are%20gathered%20together%20for%20the%20holiday%20season%20this%20year%20than%20they%20did%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%20when%20COVID-19%20was%20a%20more%20immediate%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20more%20outbreaks%2C%20people%20are%20unmasked%2C%20people%20are%20engaging%20with%20each%20other%2C%20they're%20not%20cleaning%20their%20hands%2C%20clearly%2C%26quot%3B%20Gohil%20said.%20%26quot%3BCleaning%20and%20disinfection%20and%20all%20that%20stuff%20is%20down.%20And%20we%20need%20to%20shore%20those%20practices%20back%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20were%20also%20years%20when%20norovirus%20outbreaks%20spiked%20just%20like%20they%20are%20now%2C%20and%20fluctuations%20like%20this%20are%20normal%2C%20Gohil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20has%20an%20important%20role%20to%20play%20in%20helping%20prevent%20the%20spread%20of%20norovirus%2C%20Gohil%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20literally%2C%20just%20by%20being%20careful%20yourself%2C%20save%20other%20people's%20lives%20indirectly.%20That's%20really%2C%20really%20important%20for%20people%20to%20understand%2C%20that%20you%20live%20in%20a%20community%2C%20%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20that%20you%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20care%2C%20and%20to%20keep%20yourself%20clean%2C%20and%20keep%20others%20safe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20wash%20your%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-norovirus-outbreak-so-bad-treatment-symptoms-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736206769000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.