%20linked%20to%20the%20current%20outbreak%20of%20H5N1%2C%20avian%20influenza.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-pig-h5n1-bird-flu-possible-human-outbreak-risk-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBird%20flu%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20claimed%20its%20first%20human%20death%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Louisiana%20patient%20died%20from%20a%20severe%20case%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh5n1-avian-bird-flu-virus-human-outbreak-pandemic-concerns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH5N1%20avian%20influenza%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20state%20health%20officials%20reported%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20patient%2C%20who%20was%20over%2065%20and%20had%20underlying%20conditions%2C%20is%20the%20only%20human%20case%20of%20H5N1%20in%20Louisiana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20still%20no%20sign%20that%20the%20H5N1%20virus%20can%20spread%20between%20people.%20The%20Louisiana%20patient%20contracted%20the%20virus%20after%20exposure%20to%20wild%20birds%20and%20a%20non-commercial%20backyard%20flock%2C%20officials%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bird%20flu's%20proliferation%20through%20bird%20and%20animal%20populations%20worldwide%20has%20led%20to%20many%20human%20spillover%20cases%20over%20the%20years.%20There%20have%20been%20939%20cases%20of%20human%20H5N1%20infections%20worldwide%20as%20of%20November%202024%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization.%20Of%20those%2C%20464%20were%20fatal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20pretty%20clear%20that%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20see%20severe%20disease%2C%26quot%3B%20Richard%20Webby%2C%20a%20virologist%20at%20St.%20Jude%20and%20director%20of%20the%20WHO%20animal%20and%20bird%20flu%20center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20guess%20the%20real%20question%20is%20are%20we%20going%20to%20see%20more%3F%20I%20don't%20know%20the%20answer%20to%20that%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ba36