is%20that%20some%20may%20take%20advantage%20of%20insider%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Rep.%20Andy%20Ogles%20of%20Tennessee%2C%20another%20Freedom%20Caucus%20letter%20signatory%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20gesture%20to%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20look%2C%20we're%20not%20treated%20any%20differently.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20widespread%20agreement%20on%20the%20principle%2C%20the%20details%20of%20an%20eventual%20ban%20aren't%20widely%20agreed%20upon%2C%20and%20different%20bills%20propose%20different%20things.%20Some%20legislation%20would%20ban%20the%20ownership%20of%20stocks%20altogether%2C%20but%20Ogles%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bactive%20day-trading%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20real%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20can't%20%3Cem%3Eown%3C%2Fem%3E%20stock%2C%20so%20that%20you%20can't%20have%20mutual%20funds%2C%26quot%3B%20Ogles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20some%20House%20Freedom%20Caucus%20members%20still%20trade%20stocks%2C%20and%20one%20%E2%80%94%20Rep.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbyron-donalds-stock-trades-insider-trading-ethics-complaint-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EByron%20Donalds%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%20violated%20a%20federal%20law%20requiring%20timely%20disclosure%20of%20stock%20trades%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20September%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcampaignlegal.org%2Fupdate%2Fcongressional-stock-trading-continues-raise-conflicts-interest-concerns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%20found%20that%2044%25%20of%20House%20members%20and%2054%25%20of%20senators%20own%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffreedom-caucus-stock-trading-ban-congress-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736197585000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A