untry%20for%20a%20stamp%20of%20renewal.%20This%20was%20a%20long-pending%20concern%20raised%20by%20professionals%20under%20this%20visa%20programme%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20Indians.%20Besides%20the%20inconvenience%20of%20traveling%20half%20way%20around%20the%20world%20and%20spending%20lakhs%20of%20rupees%20on%20air%20tickets%2C%20the%20process%20was%20a%20tedious%20one%20involving%20the%20applicant%20to%20wait%20for%20a%20confirmed%20visa%20appointment%20which%20often%20led%20to%20long%20wait-times%20and%20subsequent%20delays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20of%20the%20pilot%20project%20was%20to%20make%20the%20renewal%20process%20fast%20and%20convenient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20declaration%20made%20in%20its%20year-end%20press%20statement%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20State%20said%20the%20pilot%20project%20for%20H-1B%20renewal%20%26quot%3Ballowed%20many%20specialty%20occupation%20workers%20from%20India%20to%20renew%20their%20visas%20without%20leaving%20the%20United%20States.%20This%20pilot%20program%20streamlined%20the%20renewal%20process%20for%20thousands%20of%20applicants%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20State%20is%20working%20to%20formally%20establish%20a%20US-based%20renewal%20program%20in%202025.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20new%20process%20has%20been%20confirmed%20to%20start%20this%20year%2C%20a%20date%20from%20which%20the%20it%20will%20officially%20begin%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20there%20is%20an%20intense%20debate%20over%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20and%20its%20job%20market%20impact%20for%20American%20citizens.%20The%20hard-right%20have%20urged%20incoming%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20end%20the%20programme%20along%20with%20his%20other%20plans%20of%20curbing%20immigration.%20Many%20argue%20that%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20holders%20%26quot%3Btake%20away%20American%20jobs%26quot%3B%20and%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bthreat%20to%20western%20civilisation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20his%20top%20officials%20including%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy%20have%20backed%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20programme%20saying%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20needs%20talented%20people%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20the%20H-1B%20allows%20for%20the%20world's%20top%20talent%20to%20live%20and%20work%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20helps%20the%20United%20States%20stay%20ahead%20of%20the%20global%20curve%20on%20technology%2C%20research%2C%20and%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20tops%20the%20list%20of%20H-1B%20visa%20holders%20globally%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20work%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20followed%20by%20medical%20and%20research.%20According%20to%20US%20State%20Department%20data%20from%202022%2C%20as%20much%20as%2077%20per%20cent%20of%203%2C20%2C000%20H-1B%20visa%20applications%20went%20to%20Indians.%20In%202023%20too%2C%20out%20of%203%2C86%2C000%20visas%2C%20more%20than%2072%20per%20cent%20were%20issued%20to%20Indian%20nationals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%203%2C31%2C000%20student%20visas%20in%202024%20alone%2C%20Indians%20now%20account%20for%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20international%20students%20pursuing%20a%20professional%20degree%20or%20higher%20education%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20further%20said%20that%20in%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20visitor%20numbers%20from%20India%20have%20increased%20by%20five%20times%2C%20and%20more%20than%20two%20million%20Indians%20traveled%20to%20the%20United%20States%20in%20the%20first%20eleven%20months%20of%202024%2C%20a%2026%20percent%20increase%20over%20the%20same%20period%20in%202023.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736176260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-01%2Fstatue-of-liberty_650x400_61516584069.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fh-1b-visa-renewal-to-get-major-boost-in-2025-indians-to-benefit-most-7413667%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Highly-skilled%20profess